comment.narrative:
- 76 planning frameworks, legislation and regulations developed that integrate the poverty-environment nexus to enhance capacity to apply integrated approaches and tools for mainstreaming environmental sustainability and climate objectives into development planning and budgeting; 
- 7 government-led inter-sectoral coordination mechanisms established and supported that promote coherence of planning, frameworks, legislation and regulations; 
- Data collected in 5 countries on environmental, social and economic data, analyzed and reported applying a poverty-environment nexus perspective through national development and SDG monitoring systems;
- 18 guidelines and tools developed to manage private sector investment decisions that facilitate or prioritize quality investments; 
- 2 Countries with increased annual and medium-term sector budget allocations (including national and sub-national levels) reflecting environmental sustainability and climate for poverty eradication.
- 2 regional and global PEA partner programmes and agencies applied an integrated mainstreaming approach.
